# Changelog


## 1.2.1 ‚Äî 2026-03-14

- Fixed routing overlap: implementer description now leads with execution, not research
- Skill descriptions (`feedback`, `workshop`) rewritten as positive triggers ("Use when‚Ä¶") instead of negative constraints ("Only invoke when‚Ä¶")
- Code-reviewer dispatch entry in `tab.md` now notes "Runs in background", consistent with other specialists
- Workshop skill references `tab:code-reviewer` by fully qualified name instead of bare "code-reviewer"
- Researcher frontmatter description expanded to include all trigger cases from `tab.md` dispatch table
- README updated to include researcher specialist in project layout and "How Agents Work"


## 1.2.0 ‚Äî 2026-03-14

- New `researcher` specialist ‚Äî scans codebases, searches the web, and gathers prior art; runs in background on Sonnet
- Specialist dispatch switched from Skill tool to Agent tool (`subagent_type: "tab:<name>"`)
- `code-reviewer` specialist gains `background: true` frontmatter
- Workshop skill now dispatches specialists for deep research and code review instead of doing it inline
- `CLAUDE.md` streamlined ‚Äî collapsed redundant design principles and conventions into concise bullet lists


## 1.1.0 ‚Äî 2026-03-13

- `tab.md` expanded to be self-sufficient ‚Äî full session-start behavior, readiness signals, and status spec now live in the agent definition instead of depending on `CLAUDE.md` for runtime behavior
- `feedback` skill now includes explicit letter grading (A‚ÄìF) as described in README
- README contributor section updated to document specialists (`code-reviewer`, `implementer`) and hub-spoke architecture
- Removed dangling `draft` and `template` skill references from agent definition
- Specialist template in `CLAUDE.md` now documents `background` and `permissionMode` frontmatter fields
- Implementer specialist gains `background: true` and `permissionMode: acceptEdits` frontmatter


## 1.0.5 ‚Äî 2026-03-11

- Unified all skill output under `.tab/work/<topic>/` ‚Äî workshops write `plan.md`, drafts write `draft-<concern>.md`, templates write `template-<pattern>.md`; no more per-skill silos
- Status entries now link to topic directories instead of individual files; session-start sync updated to scan `.tab/work/` for topic directories
- Dropped date-prefixed filenames ‚Äî output paths are topic-scoped, not time-scoped
- `CLAUDE.md` updated to reflect new directory conventions


## 1.0.4 ‚Äî 2026-03-11

- New `template` skill ‚Äî guided interview that produces reusable reference docs for recurring types of work; includes discovery phase, readiness check, and coverage confirmation before drafting
- `feedback` skill sharpened: added explicit Filter step before delivery ("would I act on this?"), trimmed Deliver step to remove redundancy


## 1.0.3 ‚Äî 2026-03-11

- `blueprint` skill renamed to `draft` ‚Äî reframed as iterative proposed-changes doc rather than auditable step list; output format is now `### Proposed Changes` with inline em-dash rationale
- Guard secrets moved from Guidance to Hard Boundaries ‚Äî makes the no-override contract explicit
- Workflow section rewritten as four named principles: Read the doc, One suggestion, Earn the introduction, Design problems go back to workshop
- Workshop doc format updated: `Key Decisions` replaced with per-idea status blocks carrying confidence, date, and three readiness heuristics (complete, reasoning, scoped)


## 1.0.2 ‚Äî 2026-03-11

- `explain` skill is now always inline ‚Äî no file output. Explanations live in the conversation.


## 1.0.1 ‚Äî 2026-03-11

- Formalized skill forking via `context: fork` frontmatter, replacing ad-hoc subagent convention
- Status file is now a running log ‚Äî completed items move to "Done" instead of being deleted
- Added session-start sync: scans `.tab/` subdirectories and adds untracked files to status
- Cleaned up README skill sections ‚Äî removed trigger lines, kept slash commands
- Aligned draw-dino description to reactive trigger convention

## 1.0.0 ‚Äî 2026-03-11

Initial release.

- Tab persona ‚Äî voice, rules, behaviors, session-to-session status tracking
- Five skills: workshop, blueprint, feedback, explain, draw-dino
- Plugin manifest and settings for automatic persona activation
- Created lightweight `.tab/status.md` workbench model
- CLAUDE.md scoped to contributor guidance
